title: Art Institute of Chicago Wooden Coordinates Keychain
description:
Keychain image Longitude and Latitude designed exclusively for the Art Institute of Chicago by Ron Kirkpatrick & Helen Maria Nugent.  In celebration of the opening of the Modern Wing by Renzo Piano.

The wood used to make this keychain is from urban trees cut due to circumstance-- construction, disease, or nuisance-- NOT timber value.  Urban wood is a source of lumber that is entirely sustainable and does not contribute to deforestation or environmental destruction.

  • Dimensions: .25 x 2.8124 x .125 in. 
  • Materials: Reclaimed wood.
